      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "King Solomon’s.—Literally, Who were to king Solomon. Kings, who were over the work for Solomon. Clearly the latter has been corrupted into the form presented by our text through a confusion of mĕlākāh, “work,” with mèlek, “king.”",
        "children": [
