        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "2Ch 8:7-11. The Canaanites Made Tributaries.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "7. all the people that were left, &c.—The descendants of the Canaanites who remained in the country were treated as war prisoners, being obliged to \"pay tribute or to serve as galley slaves\" (2Ch 2:18), while the Israelites were employed in no works but such as were of an honorable character.",
        "children": []
